node.text:
🚨FOR ALL UPCOMING OUTDOOR SHOWS🚨

THIS DOES NOT APPLY TO DINING

In the interest of keeping our guests and staff protected and healthy, Alex G and Pappy + Harriet’s will now require all attendees of Alex G’s upcoming show on Saturday August 7th to show proof of either a full COVID-19 vaccination or negative COVID-19 PCR test result.
🚨THIS APPLIES TO ALL SHOWS GOING FORWARD🚨
Refunds applies to shows that are, "Presented by Pappy + Harriets." 
Contact Hello@pappyandharriets.com

PLEASE CHECK YOUR TICKETS CAREFULLY AND CONTACT OUTSIDE PROMOTERS WHO YOU BOUGHT TICKETS THROUGH FOR REFUNDS
 
You can find your record here:
https://myvaccinerecord.cdph.ca.gov

All attendees will be required to show one of the following for entry at Pappy + Harriet’s on August 7th along with a government issued ID:

•	Your vaccine card
•	A clear and legible photocopy of your vaccine card
•	Photo of your vaccine card on your phone
•	A digital vaccine passport or record
•	A negative COVID-19 PCR test result obtained within 72 hours of the event
 
In addition, we are asking all patrons to do the following while on site: Comply with the Pappy + Harriet’s Fan Health Pledge and wear a mask whenever indoors.
 
If you purchased a ticket and are not vaccinated and cannot get tested, we will happily refund your money. Please e-mail hello@pappyandharriets.com with your confirmation number and we will immediately issue a refund.
 
Any other questions should be directed to hello@pappyandharriets.com

Foo Fighters Approved Rock!

This wickedly fun band is opening for the Foo Fighters in November and Pappy’s gets them fresh off that that Mexico City date! The LA times compared the compelling lead singer to, “moving like a wick on a smoking firecracker.” 
The music ranges from melancholy ’80s post-punk to ’90s grunge Intense, but with a veil of dreaminess.

and Bad Waitress

node.text:
SATURDAY NIGHT COUNTRY GOLD!
FREE!
7.31.21
9 PM!

Leroy from the North is the brain child of long time songwriter, sideman and session player Eli Wulfmeier.
The LA based, Americana/rock band could best be described as a velour track suit with a Cowboy hat influenced by the sounds of '70s country gold, mixed with a little Detroit steel, Leroy is just a short dune buggy ride away from the nearest YMCA or above ground pool.

Look out for Eli in his acting debut as a supporting cast member in the movie 'Rusty' that was released on Amazon this fall. Eli also was responsible for the amazing score in this film.

The band's first full-length album will be released in 2021.

node.text:
Son Lux is a geographically and culturally diverse band that will bring their unique sonic approach to create an otherworldly experience to our inside stage. The balance of raw emotional intimacy and meticulous constructions of post-rock and electronica heavily influences their latest release, “Tomorrows,” a long format album and the final album of their trilogy that's full of emotion and pounding drama from beginning to end!

Show: Tuesday, May 17th, 2022 
Tickets on Sale: Friday, July 30th @ 9am PST

SATURDAY NIGHT FREE MUSIC AT PAPPYS! 
OUTLAW COUNTRY!
9 pm!

Herb Benham IV has created a musical intersection between his Bakersfield, CA outlaw country roots and the cosmic rock and roll psychedelia of the Mojave desert. Traces of stadium rock, psychedelic folk, and more can be heard, but Herb’s sound is entirely his own. Look no further for the future of California country.

node.text:
Lucinda Williams was the first major artist booked at Pappy + Harriets in the aughts. She is the roots of the legendary music venue P+H has become, and her story is told often, and affectionately, around these parts. 

To have her back is truly full circle, and her recent words hammer it home. “It’s all come full circle,” says Lucinda Williams about her powerful new album, Good Souls Better Angels. After more than forty years of music making, the pioneering, Louisiana-born artist has returned to the gritty blues foundation that first inspired her as a young singer-songwriter in the late 1970s. 
Lucinda will draw from all corners of her catalogue for what will be a revelatory, magical night under the stars in the High Desert.

Cass McCombs Band, lead by the stunning, ingenious singer/songwriter supports. Cass has released nine full-length albums with his most recent “Tip of the Sphere” by ANTI-Records. We couldn’t ask for more!
We are honored and thrilled to be able to bring this incredible night to Pioneertown.

Show: Monday, October 18, 2021
@ Pappy + Harriet's Pioneertown Palace on our starlit, outdoor stage!
Tickets on Sale: 
Friday, July 23rd @11 am
